sql:

  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct,

    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)),

sql:
select  
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  nation
    inner join nation
      inner join nation
      on (nation.n_comment = nation.n_comment )
    on (nation.n_nationkey is not NULL)
where nation.n_comment is not NULL
limit 101;
nl: What are the unique nation keys and comments for a sample of 101 nations that have a comment?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  region.r_name, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  region.r_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice
from 
  region
    inner join lineitem
      inner join supplier
      on (lineitem.l_tax = supplier.s_acctbal )
    on (lineitem.l_receiptdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
where lineitem.l_partkey <= region.r_regionkey
limit 126;
nl: What are the receipt dates, taxes, comments, and extended prices of orders from suppliers in specific regions, along with the supplier names, addresses, and regional information?

sql:

  lineitem.l_linestatus

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal
from 
  lineitem
    inner join orders
        inner join region
          inner join orders
            inner join part
            on (orders.o_custkey = part.p_partkey )
          on (part.p_size <= region.r_regionkey)
        on (part.p_retailprice = orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join supplier
      on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is not NULL)
where orders.o_clerk <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct;
nl: What are the return flags, order keys, and account balances for suppliers where the total price of an order is less than or equal to the retail price of a part, and the clerk who took the order has a lower identifier than the shipping instructions?

nl: What are the comments, supply costs, and corresponding part and supplier keys for a specific set of 87 parts with known supply costs?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_custkey
from 
  lineitem
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_suppkey < lineitem.l_suppkey)
      inner join customer
        inner join customer
          inner join part
          on (customer.c_custkey < customer.c_nationkey)
        on (customer.c_nationkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
      on (customer.c_nationkey <= customer.c_custkey)
    inner join lineitem
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join partsupp
            inner join supplier
            on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
          inner join lineitem
          on (supplier.s_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        on (orders.o_custkey <= orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join customer
          inner join part
          on (customer.c_nationkey = part.p_partkey )
        inner join part
        on (part.p_brand = customer.c_mktsegment)
      on (orders.o_orderdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (part.p_size is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL;
nl: What are the customer keys for customers who have placed orders with a specified priority?

sql:

  orders.o_orderdate, 
  part.p_type
from 
  orders

          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join part
      on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_returnflag is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipdate is not NULL
limit 96;

sql:
select  
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  nation.n_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid)), 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval"))
from 
  orders
        inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_custkey)
        on (orders.o_shippriority <= orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join partsupp
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_comment = region.r_comment )
          inner join nation
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_name > region.r_name)
      on (nation.n_name > orders.o_orderstatus)
    inner join nation
      inner join part
      on (nation.n_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey)
    on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
where supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone
limit 70;
nl: What is the minimum cost, comment about a nation, minimum order identifier, and total time interval for the 70 most recent orders?

  customer.c_address,

    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)),

  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8))
from 
  nation
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey <= lineitem.l_orderkey)
      inner join customer
      on (nation.n_regionkey = customer.c_custkey )
    inner join lineitem
    on (lineitem.l_commitdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
where lineitem.l_orderkey >= nation.n_nationkey;

sql:

where lineitem.l_receiptdate is NULL;

sql:
select  
  part.p_partkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  region
    inner join supplier
        inner join supplier
        on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join orders
            inner join part
            on (orders.o_orderstatus < orders.o_orderstatus)
          inner join part
            inner join partsupp
            on (part.p_size > part.p_size)
          on (partsupp.ps_suppkey > part.p_size)
        inner join nation
        on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL
limit 78;
nl: What are the part keys and corresponding nation keys for a specific set of suppliers, orders, and parts that meet certain conditions?

sql:

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  partsupp
        inner join part
        on (part.p_brand >= part.p_mfgr)
      inner join region
      on (part.p_size < region.r_regionkey)
    inner join orders
    on (orders.o_custkey is NULL)
where orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_custkey
limit 132;
nl: What are the part keys and retail prices of parts from certain brands and manufacturers, available in specific regions, that have been shipped with a priority matching their customer key, and what are the corresponding supplier part keys for these shipments?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  orders.o_orderpriority, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money))
from 
  nation
    inner join orders
        inner join part
            inner join orders
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_name <= supplier.s_phone)
            on (part.p_size = supplier.s_suppkey )
          inner join partsupp
          on (supplier.s_suppkey > supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (orders.o_clerk > orders.o_orderstatus)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_quantity <= orders.o_totalprice)
    on (nation.n_regionkey is NULL)
where nation.n_name is not NULL
limit 101;
nl: What are the supplier keys, line numbers, average null values, order priorities, and minimum null money values for a limited set of records where the nation name is not null?

where customer.c_phone is NULL;

where lineitem.l_shipdate is NULL

    inner join supplier
    on (region.r_regionkey is NULL)
where supplier.s_name is NULL
limit 60;
nl: What are the comments for regions that do not have a corresponding supplier name?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  avg(
    cast(lineitem.l_linenumber as int4)), 
  customer.c_name, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  avg(
    cast(lineitem.l_partkey as int4)), 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  lineitem
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_partkey <= nation.n_nationkey)
      inner join partsupp
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone)
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_discount)
          inner join region
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag < lineitem.l_shipmode)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (lineitem.l_partkey > partsupp.ps_partkey)
      on (supplier.s_suppkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)
    inner join customer
            inner join lineitem
            on (customer.c_custkey < lineitem.l_suppkey)
          inner join lineitem
            inner join region
            on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_discount)
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > lineitem.l_shipmode)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice > lineitem.l_tax)
      inner join customer
      on (lineitem.l_orderkey < customer.c_custkey)
    on (region.r_comment is NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL;
nl: What are the shipping instructions, average line numbers, customer names, commit dates, line statuses, average part keys, maximum intervals, discounts, and quantities available for each nation's market segment, along with regional comments, where the supplier's account balance is not null?

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  max(
    cast(supplier.s_nationkey as int4)), 
  avg(
    cast(supplier.s_acctbal as "numeric")), 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  supplier
where supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal
limit 94;
nl: What is the maximum and minimum account balance, average account balance, phone number, address, and name of suppliers, along with their comments and nation key?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  max(
    cast(part.p_container as bpchar)), 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_tax as "numeric")), 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_tax as "numeric"))
from 
  supplier
        inner join part
          inner join nation
              inner join nation
              on (nation.n_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey)
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_name < nation.n_name)
          on (nation.n_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
        on (supplier.s_suppkey = nation.n_nationkey )
      inner join customer
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    inner join orders
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_quantity)
        inner join supplier
          inner join partsupp
            inner join nation
              inner join part
              on (part.p_retailprice >= part.p_retailprice)
            on (nation.n_name = part.p_container)
          on (supplier.s_suppkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
        on (part.p_retailprice > lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    on (supplier.s_suppkey < partsupp.ps_partkey)
where lineitem.l_receiptdate is not NULL
limit 180;
nl: What are the commitment dates, part keys, maximum container sizes, and total taxes for a set of 180 specific orders?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_address, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  customer.c_comment
from 
  customer
    inner join supplier
    on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
where supplier.s_suppkey > customer.c_custkey;
nl: What are the addresses and account balances of suppliers, along with corresponding customer comments, where the supplier's key is greater than the customer's key?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz))
from 
  orders
    inner join region
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
    on (region.r_name is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL
limit 141;
nl: What is the total price of all orders with a specified priority, considering only those with no region assigned?

sql:

from 
  orders

      inner join orders
        inner join region
          inner join nation
          on (region.r_comment = nation.n_comment )
        on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
      on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)

sql:
select  
  region.r_regionkey, 
  orders.o_orderkey
from 
  nation
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_quantity < lineitem.l_discount)
    inner join orders
      inner join nation
            inner join region
            on (nation.n_nationkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
          inner join customer
          on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_clerk <= orders.o_orderstatus)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where nation.n_name >= orders.o_orderstatus;

    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2))
from 
  customer
        inner join region
        on (customer.c_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
      inner join part
                inner join region
                on (part.p_container < region.r_name)
              inner join supplier
              on (part.p_retailprice > supplier.s_acctbal)
            inner join part
            on (part.p_partkey >= part.p_partkey)
          inner join nation

        inner join region
          inner join region
          on (region.r_regionkey >= region.r_regionkey)
        on (part.p_retailprice > supplier.s_acctbal)

select  
  part.p_size, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_address, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  part.p_container, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  part.p_brand, 
  part.p_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  part.p_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  customer.c_name, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8))
from 
  partsupp
        inner join supplier
            inner join part
            on (part.p_retailprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join customer
            inner join customer
                inner join part
                on (part.p_mfgr > part.p_brand)
              inner join orders
              on (customer.c_acctbal < orders.o_totalprice)
            on (orders.o_orderstatus = customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (part.p_size = customer.c_custkey )
        on (customer.c_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join region
      on (supplier.s_name = customer.c_mktsegment)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join partsupp
        inner join partsupp
            inner join part
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty > partsupp.ps_suppkey)
          inner join region
          on (region.r_regionkey = partsupp.ps_availqty)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= region.r_regionkey)
      on (partsupp.ps_availqty = part.p_partkey )
    on (partsupp.ps_comment is not NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is NULL
limit 120;

      inner join region

    inner join partsupp
        inner join region
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < partsupp.ps_supplycost)

sql:
select  
  part.p_retailprice
from 
  part
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
              inner join part
              on (part.p_partkey < supplier.s_nationkey)
            on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join supplier
          on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
        inner join region
            inner join nation
            on (region.r_name < region.r_name)
          inner join part
            inner join region
              inner join region
              on (region.r_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
            on (part.p_container = region.r_name )
          on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_mfgr)
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
      on (part.p_partkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
    inner join region
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > supplier.s_phone)
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (region.r_regionkey = supplier.s_suppkey )
    on (nation.n_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
where lineitem.l_shipmode = lineitem.l_shipinstruct;

sql:
select  
  part.p_name, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_quantity as "numeric")), 
  max(
    cast(part.p_retailprice as "numeric")), 
  region.r_name, 
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_shipdate as date)), 
  part.p_container, 
  region.r_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as timestamptz) as timestamptz)), 
  supplier.s_address, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  max(
    cast(part.p_container as bpchar)), 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  supplier.s_acctbal
from 
  lineitem
    inner join part
        inner join nation
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (nation.n_nationkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join region
          on (region.r_name <= region.r_name)
        inner join region
            inner join part
            on (part.p_retailprice = part.p_retailprice)
          inner join part
          on (region.r_regionkey < part.p_partkey)
        on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= part.p_retailprice)
      on (supplier.s_phone = part.p_container)
    on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
where lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate;
nl: What are the names of parts, their supply costs, maximum quantities ordered, maximum retail prices, regions they belong to, latest shipment dates, container types, region comments, supplier addresses, order statuses, and supplier account balances?

                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
            on (lineitem.l_linenumber >= lineitem.l_partkey)
          on (lineitem.l_linestatus > customer.c_mktsegment)
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > lineitem.l_shipinstruct)

select

  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  count(
    cast(orders.o_orderdate as date)), 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  customer.c_comment, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  lineitem.l_tax, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  orders.o_orderdate
from 
  supplier
    inner join orders
        inner join lineitem
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
                inner join supplier
                on (partsupp.ps_comment = supplier.s_address )
              on (lineitem.l_orderkey < lineitem.l_orderkey)
            inner join customer
              inner join orders
                inner join lineitem
                on (orders.o_orderkey > orders.o_shippriority)
              on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
            on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct >= customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join supplier
        inner join customer
          inner join part
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
          on (customer.c_comment = customer.c_name )
        on (part.p_retailprice > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate < orders.o_orderdate)
    on (part.p_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_linenumber is not NULL;

  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  part.p_container, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_clerk, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as anyenum) as anyenum))
from 
  part
    inner join lineitem
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join supplier
          inner join orders
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_suppkey = supplier.s_nationkey)
          on (orders.o_orderkey > orders.o_custkey)
        on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
      inner join nation
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct <= nation.n_name)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is NULL)
where supplier.s_suppkey = part.p_size
limit 57;
nl: What are the details of orders, including customer information, order dates, and shipping instructions, along with the corresponding parts, suppliers, and nations, for a specific set of suppliers?

sql:
select distinct 
  region.r_comment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid)), 
  part.p_name, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  part.p_type
from 
  customer
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey = part.p_size)
      on (lineitem.l_quantity <= lineitem.l_tax)
    inner join lineitem
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_custkey)
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct = lineitem.l_linestatus)
        inner join part
          inner join region
          on (part.p_brand >= region.r_name)
        on (part.p_container >= part.p_container)
      inner join nation
        inner join customer
        on (nation.n_regionkey = customer.c_custkey )
      on (lineitem.l_shipmode >= customer.c_mktsegment)
    on (part.p_container < customer.c_mktsegment)
where customer.c_address is NULL;
nl: What are the distinct region comments, part names, line item statuses, commit dates, and part types for customers with no address?

sql:
select  
  customer.c_comment, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  customer.c_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  region.r_regionkey
from 
  customer
    inner join customer
      inner join supplier
          inner join region
          on (region.r_name > supplier.s_phone)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = supplier.s_suppkey)
      on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_suppkey is not NULL)
where part.p_partkey <= customer.c_custkey
limit 110;
nl: What are the comments, customer keys, names, region keys, nation keys, and account balances of customers who have suppliers with a certain account balance, and are located in regions with specific names, along with the corresponding supplier account balances and region keys?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_comment, 
  orders.o_orderdate, 
  region.r_name, 
  nation.n_name, 
  region.r_comment, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  region.r_name
from 
  orders
      inner join orders
          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_orderkey = nation.n_nationkey )
        inner join customer
        on (orders.o_clerk = customer.c_phone )
      on (customer.c_phone > orders.o_orderstatus)
    inner join supplier
      inner join partsupp
          inner join orders
              inner join region
              on (region.r_name >= orders.o_orderpriority)
            inner join supplier
              inner join part
              on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
            on (region.r_comment = part.p_name )
          on (part.p_retailprice >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_name > part.p_brand)
      on (partsupp.ps_availqty <= part.p_partkey)
    on (supplier.s_comment is NULL)
where orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL;
nl: What are the order comments, dates, and shipping priorities, along with the corresponding region names, nation names, and region comments, for all orders that have a priority?

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  part.p_brand, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")), 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  avg(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_container, 
  part.p_size
from 
  part
        inner join supplier
        on (part.p_size <= supplier.s_nationkey)
      inner join part
            inner join part
            on (part.p_comment = part.p_name )
          inner join region
          on (part.p_comment = region.r_comment )
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_nationkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
      on (part.p_size < region.r_regionkey)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join supplier
      on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
    on (part.p_size < supplier.s_suppkey)
where part.p_retailprice >= partsupp.ps_supplycost;

    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid))
from

          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_nationkey < nation.n_nationkey)
        inner join region
          inner join lineitem
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_linenumber > lineitem.l_orderkey)
          on (lineitem.l_quantity = lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (nation.n_name = region.r_name )
      inner join part
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join region
      on (region.r_name >= region.r_name)
    on (region.r_comment is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost;

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(lineitem.l_commitdate as date)), 
  region.r_comment, 
  part.p_brand, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  region.r_name
from 
  orders
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_returnflag)
          inner join region
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_mktsegment < region.r_name)
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join region
          on (lineitem.l_quantity > lineitem.l_tax)
        on (customer.c_phone >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join part
        inner join lineitem
        on (part.p_type = lineitem.l_comment )
      on (part.p_partkey > orders.o_shippriority)
    inner join orders
      inner join nation
      on (orders.o_orderpriority = nation.n_name )
    on (lineitem.l_linestatus = orders.o_orderstatus )
where orders.o_orderstatus is not NULL

where lineitem.l_shipdate is not NULL

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_phone, 
  nation.n_comment, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as xid8) as xid8)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  supplier.s_name, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as date) as date)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  nation.n_name, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  region.r_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty
from 
  nation
        inner join nation
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_nationkey > customer.c_nationkey)
        on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
      inner join region
        inner join nation
          inner join partsupp
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
      on (nation.n_regionkey <= nation.n_regionkey)
    inner join region
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_suppkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
          inner join partsupp
          on (supplier.s_acctbal <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join region
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_availqty = partsupp.ps_partkey)
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
        on (region.r_regionkey >= supplier.s_suppkey)
      on (supplier.s_name = nation.n_name)
    on (region.r_name is not NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal;

          inner join lineitem

        on (nation.n_regionkey < lineitem.l_orderkey)

sql:
select  
  nation.n_name, 
  orders.o_comment, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  supplier.s_phone
from 
  orders
      inner join part
      on (part.p_size >= orders.o_shippriority)
    inner join nation
          inner join orders
            inner join region
                inner join part
                on (region.r_name = part.p_mfgr )
              inner join nation
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
              on (lineitem.l_shipmode <= nation.n_name)
            on (part.p_retailprice < lineitem.l_discount)
          on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
        inner join supplier
        on (part.p_retailprice >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join region
      on (lineitem.l_discount <= orders.o_totalprice)

select

        on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join orders
        inner join region
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_acctbal <= customer.c_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderkey >= orders.o_orderkey)
    inner join partsupp
            inner join region
            on (region.r_regionkey = partsupp.ps_partkey)
          inner join region
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
          on (region.r_name >= orders.o_clerk)
        inner join supplier
        on (orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_orderkey)
      inner join region
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_acctbal >= customer.c_acctbal)
        inner join orders
            inner join region
              inner join nation
              on (region.r_name = nation.n_name)
            on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join part
          on (part.p_retailprice < orders.o_totalprice)
        on (part.p_retailprice > customer.c_acctbal)
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > orders.o_totalprice)
    on (orders.o_shippriority < partsupp.ps_suppkey)
where nation.n_comment is NULL;

from

            on (part.p_retailprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (lineitem.l_partkey <= supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (part.p_size = part.p_partkey)

from

      inner join supplier
        inner join customer
        on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (lineitem.l_tax < customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_comment = supplier.s_address )

select

    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  region.r_name
from 
  partsupp
    inner join nation
      inner join supplier
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_custkey <= supplier.s_suppkey)
        inner join region
              inner join customer
                inner join lineitem
                  inner join orders
                  on (orders.o_orderpriority <= orders.o_orderpriority)
                on (customer.c_acctbal = orders.o_totalprice )
              on (customer.c_acctbal < lineitem.l_tax)
            inner join customer
            on (orders.o_custkey > customer.c_nationkey)
          inner join customer
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_returnflag > lineitem.l_shipmode)
            inner join region
            on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_tax)
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus >= lineitem.l_returnflag)
      on (orders.o_totalprice >= customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_acctbal is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipinstruct is NULL

            on (part.p_retailprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
              on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderpriority >= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
          on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_quantity)
        inner join supplier
              inner join partsupp
              on (supplier.s_acctbal = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
            inner join region
              inner join customer
              on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
            on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
          inner join supplier
          on (customer.c_comment = supplier.s_address )
        on (orders.o_clerk > region.r_name)
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (supplier.s_address is not NULL)
where orders.o_totalprice < supplier.s_acctbal

sql:
select  
  customer.c_phone, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  customer.c_nationkey
from 
  customer
      inner join orders
          inner join customer
          on (orders.o_clerk = customer.c_phone)
        inner join lineitem
            inner join partsupp
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
          inner join lineitem
            inner join nation
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
            on (lineitem.l_partkey <= lineitem.l_orderkey)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (orders.o_clerk < lineitem.l_shipmode)
    inner join orders
    on (nation.n_regionkey is not NULL)
where orders.o_totalprice is NULL;
nl: What phone numbers of customers, along with their supplier keys and nation keys, have no total order price?

sql:
select  
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as "time") as "time")), 
  part.p_type, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  min(
    cast(part.p_partkey as int4)), 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  region.r_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int2) as int2)), 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  region.r_name, 
  min(
    cast(supplier.s_acctbal as "numeric")), 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  customer.c_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  orders.o_orderpriority
from 
  region
        inner join customer
        on (region.r_comment = customer.c_name )
      inner join orders
        inner join part
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (orders.o_totalprice < supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (supplier.s_phone > region.r_name)
    inner join part
          inner join region
            inner join part
            on (part.p_size >= part.p_size)
          on (part.p_size = part.p_partkey)
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join part
              inner join nation
              on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_container)
            inner join supplier
                inner join region
                on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
              inner join customer
              on (region.r_name = customer.c_phone )
            on (part.p_brand > customer.c_phone)
          inner join customer
            inner join orders
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
            on (customer.c_phone = orders.o_orderstatus)
          on (supplier.s_acctbal >= orders.o_totalprice)
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_nationkey >= customer.c_custkey)
      on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_quantity)
    on (part.p_partkey is not NULL)
where region.r_regionkey > orders.o_orderkey;
nl: What are the total prices of orders, customer information, part types, supplier phone numbers, market segments, manufacturer details, region names, retail prices, and order priorities for customers in specific regions?

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  customer.c_comment, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  customer.c_custkey, 
  nation.n_name, 
  sum(
    cast(lineitem.l_extendedprice as "numeric")), 
  orders.o_totalprice, 
  lineitem.l_returnflag, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_shipmode
from 
  customer
      inner join orders
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_clerk <= orders.o_orderpriority)
          inner join lineitem
          on (orders.o_custkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
        inner join customer
        on (lineitem.l_discount >= lineitem.l_quantity)
      on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_quantity)
    inner join nation
      inner join lineitem
        inner join nation
            inner join region
            on (nation.n_nationkey = region.r_regionkey )
          inner join lineitem
            inner join nation
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
            on (orders.o_orderstatus > lineitem.l_linestatus)
          on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus = nation.n_name)
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (region.r_regionkey >= orders.o_orderkey)
where lineitem.l_linenumber >= nation.n_nationkey
limit 100;
nl: What are the extended prices, ship dates, customer comments, return flags, phone numbers, customer keys, nation names, total extended prices, order totals, return flags, shipping priorities, and shipping modes for a selection of 100 records?

sql:
select  
  count(*), 
  lineitem.l_shipmode, 
  orders.o_clerk
from 
  customer
          inner join lineitem
          on (customer.c_acctbal < lineitem.l_extendedprice)
        inner join supplier
        on (lineitem.l_tax >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join customer
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
            inner join region
            on (orders.o_shippriority = orders.o_shippriority)
          inner join customer
          on (orders.o_shippriority = customer.c_custkey )
        on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct = customer.c_phone )
      inner join lineitem
        inner join part
          inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
              on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_discount)
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < lineitem.l_discount)
          on (part.p_type = region.r_comment )
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (lineitem.l_partkey > region.r_regionkey)
    on (lineitem.l_shipmode is NULL)
where lineitem.l_orderkey is NULL
limit 145;
nl: What are the counts of shipments with unknown shipping modes, grouped by clerk and shipping mode, for orders without an assigned order key?

sql:
select distinct 
  nation.n_nationkey
from 
  supplier
    inner join nation
      inner join supplier
        inner join lineitem
          inner join orders
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_orderkey = lineitem.l_partkey)
            inner join part
                inner join partsupp
                on (part.p_size = partsupp.ps_partkey )
              inner join customer
                inner join lineitem
                  inner join nation
                  on (lineitem.l_linenumber > nation.n_regionkey)
                on (customer.c_nationkey <= lineitem.l_linenumber)
              on (part.p_partkey = customer.c_custkey)
            on (orders.o_totalprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
          on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_quantity)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal = lineitem.l_discount)
      on (partsupp.ps_suppkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
    on (lineitem.l_shipdate is NULL)
where lineitem.l_extendedprice is NULL
limit 82;
nl: What nations have suppliers that are associated with orders and parts, but do not have a ship date or extended price?

sql:
select  
  nation.n_comment
from 
  nation
      inner join nation
        inner join region
            inner join supplier
            on (region.r_regionkey = region.r_regionkey)
          inner join orders
          on (supplier.s_name > region.r_name)
        on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
      on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_orderkey )
    inner join lineitem
        inner join supplier
        on (lineitem.l_linenumber >= lineitem.l_partkey)
      inner join partsupp
      on (lineitem.l_orderkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
    on (orders.o_custkey is NULL)
where supplier.s_acctbal is NULL
limit 102;

sql:
select  
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  customer.c_address, 
  nation.n_name, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_linestatus, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  region.r_name, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  max(
    cast(supplier.s_name as bpchar)), 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  orders.o_orderkey
from 
  partsupp
    inner join supplier
      inner join lineitem
          inner join partsupp
              inner join region
                inner join customer
                on (customer.c_custkey > region.r_regionkey)
              on (customer.c_custkey >= customer.c_custkey)
            inner join nation
            on (customer.c_phone >= customer.c_mktsegment)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate >= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
        inner join orders
            inner join partsupp
            on (orders.o_totalprice < partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          inner join partsupp
          on (orders.o_clerk = orders.o_orderstatus)
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey >= partsupp.ps_availqty)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal )
    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty is NULL
limit 137;

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_suppkey, 
  customer.c_address, 
  supplier.s_name, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty
from 
  supplier
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_partkey > supplier.s_suppkey)
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join region
              inner join partsupp
              on (partsupp.ps_availqty = region.r_regionkey)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join region
            inner join nation
              inner join supplier
              on (supplier.s_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
            on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
          on (orders.o_shippriority < region.r_regionkey)
        on (lineitem.l_linestatus <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join orders
        inner join part
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
          inner join nation
          on (lineitem.l_discount >= lineitem.l_discount)
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
      on (supplier.s_nationkey = nation.n_regionkey)
    inner join customer
        inner join customer
        on (customer.c_mktsegment <= customer.c_phone)
      inner join supplier
      on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
    on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_name )
where nation.n_regionkey is not NULL;
nl: What are the shipping instructions, region keys, supplier keys, customer addresses, supplier names, and available quantities for each line item, along with the corresponding order details?

sql:
select

  nation.n_name, 
  customer.c_address, 
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  lineitem.l_quantity, 
  lineitem.l_linenumber, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_name
from 
  customer
            inner join region
            on (customer.c_phone = region.r_name)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_returnflag >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
      inner join nation
              inner join customer
              on (nation.n_name < customer.c_mktsegment)
            inner join partsupp
            on (customer.c_mktsegment < customer.c_mktsegment)
          inner join lineitem
              inner join customer
                inner join supplier
                on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
              on (lineitem.l_tax <= customer.c_acctbal)
            inner join orders
            on (lineitem.l_discount <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
          on (supplier.s_nationkey >= customer.c_nationkey)
        inner join part
        on (part.p_size > nation.n_nationkey)
      on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
    inner join partsupp
            inner join lineitem
            on (lineitem.l_quantity >= lineitem.l_tax)
          inner join lineitem
          on (partsupp.ps_partkey = lineitem.l_orderkey )
        inner join customer
            inner join lineitem
            on (customer.c_name = lineitem.l_comment )
          inner join partsupp
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag <= customer.c_mktsegment)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
      inner join orders
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag > orders.o_orderpriority)
    on (customer.c_acctbal is NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL

      inner join nation
          inner join partsupp

            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)

        inner join region

    inner join lineitem
          inner join orders

            on (region.r_name >= orders.o_orderstatus)
          on (lineitem.l_suppkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
        inner join customer
        on (lineitem.l_partkey >= lineitem.l_linenumber)
      inner join customer
        inner join partsupp
        on (customer.c_phone = customer.c_mktsegment)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)
    on (region.r_regionkey is not NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate
limit 118;

sql:

    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")),

    cast(cast(null as "interval") as "interval")),

  partsupp.ps_availqty,

  lineitem.l_shipdate
from 
  lineitem
    inner join region
      inner join partsupp
      on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
where region.r_comment is NULL
limit 113;

from

nl: What are the names of regions, along with their corresponding suppliers' account balances and names, where the supplier's phone number is not available?

sql:
select  
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  part.p_brand, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  lineitem.l_commitdate, 
  orders.o_orderkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  part.p_type, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  lineitem.l_orderkey, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  customer.c_phone
from 
  lineitem
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_discount > lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join customer
          inner join region
          on (customer.c_name = region.r_comment )
        on (lineitem.l_tax <= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
      inner join orders
          inner join customer
              inner join supplier
              on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
            inner join customer
              inner join part
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_commitdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
              on (lineitem.l_receiptdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
            on (lineitem.l_tax >= lineitem.l_quantity)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_nationkey = customer.c_custkey)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal >= orders.o_totalprice)
    inner join partsupp
    on (region.r_name is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_orderkey is not NULL
limit 105;
nl: What are the account balances, brands, region keys, supply costs, commit dates, order keys, phone numbers, part types, nation keys, and customer account balances for a specific set of orders?

sql:
select  
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  customer.c_comment
from 
  supplier
        inner join customer
          inner join partsupp
              inner join partsupp
              on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
            inner join partsupp
            on (partsupp.ps_comment = partsupp.ps_comment )
          on (customer.c_acctbal = partsupp.ps_supplycost )
        on (customer.c_acctbal <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      inner join customer
        inner join partsupp
          inner join part
          on (part.p_size <= partsupp.ps_partkey)
        on (part.p_partkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)
      on (part.p_container < customer.c_mktsegment)
    inner join supplier
        inner join part
        on (supplier.s_phone <= supplier.s_name)
      inner join lineitem
        inner join orders
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_custkey = orders.o_custkey)
        on (lineitem.l_quantity = orders.o_totalprice )
      on (lineitem.l_partkey >= supplier.s_nationkey)
    on (partsupp.ps_comment is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_partkey is NULL
limit 108;

              inner join orders
              on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct > orders.o_orderstatus)
            on (lineitem.l_extendedprice >= lineitem.l_discount)
          inner join part
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_custkey <= customer.c_nationkey)
          on (part.p_mfgr > orders.o_clerk)
        inner join lineitem
          inner join supplier
          on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
        on (customer.c_acctbal <= lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join lineitem
      on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct < lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    inner join orders
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
    on (lineitem.l_quantity is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_linestatus <= orders.o_clerk
limit 67;

          inner join partsupp

        inner join lineitem

      inner join orders
          inner join lineitem

        inner join part

          inner join lineitem

            on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)

sql:

  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  customer.c_acctbal, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost
from 
  partsupp
        inner join part
          inner join partsupp
          on (part.p_mfgr = part.p_container)
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey = part.p_partkey )
      inner join customer
        inner join partsupp
                inner join partsupp
                on (partsupp.ps_partkey > partsupp.ps_partkey)
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join partsupp
          on (orders.o_orderkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
        on (orders.o_clerk <= orders.o_orderstatus)
      on (orders.o_orderkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)
    inner join customer
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_mktsegment <= customer.c_mktsegment)
        inner join supplier
          inner join region
          on (supplier.s_comment = region.r_comment )
        on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
      inner join region
      on (region.r_name >= customer.c_phone)
    on (part.p_retailprice is NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate;

  orders.o_totalprice,

  nation.n_regionkey, 
  sum(
    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  supplier.s_name
from 
  orders
        inner join nation
          inner join orders
              inner join partsupp
                inner join partsupp
                on (partsupp.ps_availqty < partsupp.ps_suppkey)
              on (orders.o_clerk < orders.o_clerk)
            inner join supplier
            on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
          on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join part
        inner join nation
        on (part.p_brand > part.p_container)
      on (orders.o_clerk = part.p_mfgr )
    inner join nation
            inner join nation
              inner join orders
                  inner join orders
                  on (orders.o_totalprice > orders.o_totalprice)
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_linestatus = orders.o_orderstatus)
              on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_shippriority)
            on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_discount)
          inner join partsupp
            inner join nation
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (orders.o_clerk = orders.o_orderpriority)
        inner join orders
        on (lineitem.l_shipdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join orders
      on (nation.n_name = orders.o_orderstatus )
    on (part.p_mfgr = orders.o_orderstatus )

select

    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  lineitem
            inner join part
            on (lineitem.l_shipinstruct >= lineitem.l_linestatus)
          inner join part
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey < lineitem.l_suppkey)
        inner join nation
        on (lineitem.l_discount <= part.p_retailprice)
      inner join nation
          inner join part
              inner join part
              on (part.p_partkey = part.p_partkey )
            inner join customer
              inner join region
              on (customer.c_nationkey > region.r_regionkey)
            on (customer.c_nationkey < part.p_size)
          on (part.p_retailprice > part.p_retailprice)
        inner join lineitem
        on (part.p_retailprice = lineitem.l_quantity )
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    inner join partsupp
      inner join part
      on (part.p_brand < part.p_mfgr)
    on (part.p_mfgr is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_commitdate is NULL;

from 
  lineitem
        inner join orders
        on (lineitem.l_quantity = orders.o_totalprice )
      inner join lineitem

          inner join supplier

    inner join nation
        inner join partsupp
            inner join lineitem

          inner join nation
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)

      inner join part

          inner join partsupp

              inner join nation
              on (nation.n_regionkey = nation.n_nationkey )
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (part.p_brand <= part.p_brand)

            on (supplier.s_acctbal <= supplier.s_acctbal)
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join partsupp
          inner join part
            inner join region
            on (part.p_retailprice > part.p_retailprice)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost < part.p_retailprice)
        on (lineitem.l_orderkey >= supplier.s_nationkey)
      on (part.p_retailprice <= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
    inner join supplier
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_name <= supplier.s_name)
        inner join part
        on (nation.n_nationkey = part.p_partkey )
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
    on (orders.o_orderstatus is not NULL)
where lineitem.l_receiptdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate;
nl: What manufacturers have parts with a retail price higher than their supply cost, and are supplied by companies from nations with a specific name, to customers who have received orders with a receipt date later than the commit date?

select

  part.p_comment
from 
  orders
        inner join supplier
        on (orders.o_clerk = supplier.s_name )
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join part
              inner join partsupp
                inner join part
                on (partsupp.ps_partkey <= partsupp.ps_suppkey)
              on (part.p_partkey < part.p_size)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join orders
          on (part.p_size <= orders.o_orderkey)
        inner join part
          inner join lineitem
            inner join orders
              inner join customer
              on (orders.o_orderpriority < orders.o_orderstatus)
            on (lineitem.l_receiptdate < lineitem.l_commitdate)
          on (part.p_size < part.p_size)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join nation
      on (orders.o_orderstatus = nation.n_name )
    on (orders.o_orderpriority is not NULL)
where customer.c_mktsegment is not NULL;

  nation.n_nationkey, 
  part.p_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey
from

      inner join part

        on (part.p_brand = nation.n_name )

            inner join part

          inner join supplier
            inner join region
              inner join part
              on (part.p_retailprice < part.p_retailprice)
            on (supplier.s_phone < supplier.s_name)
          on (part.p_container = part.p_mfgr)
        inner join nation
          inner join supplier
          on (nation.n_regionkey >= supplier.s_nationkey)
        on (supplier.s_suppkey > supplier.s_nationkey)

where region.r_comment is NULL

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as "timestamp") as "timestamp")), 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as text) as text)), 
  lineitem.l_extendedprice, 
  orders.o_shippriority, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  region.r_comment, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct
from 
  orders
        inner join customer
        on (orders.o_shippriority >= customer.c_custkey)
      inner join orders
        inner join orders
          inner join orders
            inner join lineitem
            on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
          on (lineitem.l_commitdate > orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate )
      on (customer.c_nationkey = lineitem.l_suppkey)
    inner join region
        inner join orders
            inner join region
              inner join orders
              on (region.r_name >= orders.o_orderpriority)
            on (region.r_name < region.r_name)
          inner join nation
            inner join partsupp
            on (nation.n_regionkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
          on (region.r_name >= region.r_name)
        on (region.r_name < orders.o_orderpriority)
      inner join lineitem
        inner join region
        on (lineitem.l_shipmode > lineitem.l_returnflag)
      on (nation.n_regionkey <= orders.o_orderkey)
    on (lineitem.l_shipdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
where customer.c_acctbal is not NULL

sql:
select  
  max(
    cast(cast(null as float4) as float4)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  nation.n_nationkey, 
  supplier.s_nationkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_shipdate, 
  region.r_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  part.p_mfgr, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  lineitem.l_shipinstruct, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty,

    cast(cast(null as anyarray) as anyarray)),

from

    inner join lineitem
              inner join partsupp
              on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_tax)
            inner join customer
              inner join supplier

          inner join nation
            inner join orders

          on (orders.o_totalprice < lineitem.l_tax)
        inner join part
              inner join region
              on (part.p_size >= part.p_partkey)
            inner join supplier
              inner join partsupp
              on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_name)
            on (part.p_container = supplier.s_name)
          inner join part
          on (supplier.s_nationkey >= region.r_regionkey)
        on (nation.n_regionkey > lineitem.l_orderkey)

sql:
select distinct 
  lineitem.l_discount, 
  supplier.s_comment, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_partkey
from 
  customer
        inner join customer
          inner join partsupp
              inner join supplier
              on (partsupp.ps_availqty = supplier.s_suppkey )
            inner join region
            on (supplier.s_name >= supplier.s_name)
          on (customer.c_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
        on (customer.c_mktsegment >= customer.c_mktsegment)
      inner join nation
        inner join supplier
        on (nation.n_nationkey >= nation.n_nationkey)
      on (supplier.s_name < customer.c_phone)
    inner join lineitem
      inner join nation
              inner join orders
                inner join partsupp
                on (orders.o_comment = partsupp.ps_comment )
              on (orders.o_orderstatus >= orders.o_clerk)
            inner join region
            on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join orders
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost = orders.o_totalprice )
        inner join part
        on (orders.o_custkey < region.r_regionkey)
      on (lineitem.l_quantity > orders.o_totalprice)
    on (orders.o_custkey is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL
limit 25;

  lineitem.l_linestatus,

    cast(orders.o_custkey as int4)),

    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn)), 
  lineitem.l_returnflag,

    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  lineitem.l_partkey,

  lineitem.l_receiptdate, 
  region.r_name, 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  partsupp
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
        inner join part
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey < partsupp.ps_availqty)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_extendedprice = partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join partsupp
            inner join part
            on (part.p_size >= part.p_size)
          inner join region
          on (part.p_retailprice >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        on (lineitem.l_extendedprice > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
      on (lineitem.l_receiptdate >= lineitem.l_receiptdate)
    inner join partsupp
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_name < nation.n_name)
        inner join region
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_mktsegment = customer.c_phone)
          inner join lineitem
          on (lineitem.l_linenumber > lineitem.l_linenumber)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate > lineitem.l_commitdate)

    on (partsupp.ps_availqty is not NULL)

select

  region.r_comment
from 
  orders
            inner join region
              inner join nation
              on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
            on (orders.o_custkey = region.r_regionkey )
          inner join customer
          on (nation.n_comment = customer.c_name )
        inner join region
        on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
      inner join supplier
      on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join partsupp
        inner join nation
          inner join customer
          on (nation.n_regionkey >= nation.n_regionkey)
        on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
      inner join partsupp
        inner join lineitem
        on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
      on (customer.c_mktsegment > lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
    on (region.r_name is NULL)
where lineitem.l_shipinstruct < customer.c_mktsegment;
nl: What regions have no name and what are their comments?

  part.p_container,

    cast(cast(null as tid) as tid)),

  part.p_mfgr

where part.p_container is not NULL

from

          inner join nation
          on (orders.o_totalprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join nation
          inner join part
          on (nation.n_regionkey = part.p_partkey )
        inner join nation
        on (part.p_retailprice < part.p_retailprice)
      on (orders.o_orderstatus = part.p_mfgr )
    inner join nation
    on (nation.n_comment is NULL)
where orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate
limit 94;

sql:
select  
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as inet) as inet)), 
  part.p_partkey, 
  partsupp.ps_comment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  orders.o_orderpriority, 
  nation.n_regionkey, 
  lineitem.l_suppkey, 
  supplier.s_acctbal, 
  supplier.s_phone, 
  nation.n_name
from 
  partsupp
          inner join lineitem
            inner join region
              inner join part
                inner join nation
                  inner join partsupp
                  on (partsupp.ps_supplycost > partsupp.ps_supplycost)
                on (part.p_mfgr > part.p_container)
              on (part.p_container < part.p_brand)
            on (region.r_name = lineitem.l_shipmode)
          on (lineitem.l_orderkey < partsupp.ps_suppkey)
        inner join orders
        on (lineitem.l_shipdate <= lineitem.l_commitdate)
      inner join partsupp
      on (lineitem.l_quantity < part.p_retailprice)
    inner join supplier
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join region
          on (supplier.s_nationkey > orders.o_shippriority)
        inner join supplier
            inner join region
              inner join orders
              on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
            on (supplier.s_acctbal < orders.o_totalprice)
          inner join nation
              inner join region
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_returnflag < lineitem.l_returnflag)
              on (nation.n_name < lineitem.l_returnflag)
            inner join partsupp
            on (nation.n_name >= nation.n_name)
          on (orders.o_orderpriority = region.r_name )
        on (supplier.s_comment = region.r_comment )
      inner join supplier
            inner join supplier
                inner join nation
                on (supplier.s_comment = nation.n_comment )
              inner join region
              on (region.r_regionkey <= region.r_regionkey)
            on (supplier.s_suppkey = nation.n_nationkey )
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_name > supplier.s_name)
        inner join supplier
          inner join supplier
          on (supplier.s_phone = supplier.s_name)
        on (supplier.s_acctbal >= supplier.s_acctbal)
      on (orders.o_custkey >= lineitem.l_orderkey)
    on (nation.n_nationkey is not NULL)
where supplier.s_comment is not NULL;

sql:
select  
  lineitem.l_partkey, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  part.p_retailprice, 
  min(
    cast(cast(null as oid) as oid))
from 
  region
      inner join supplier
      on (region.r_name >= supplier.s_phone)
    inner join customer
        inner join nation
        on (nation.n_regionkey < customer.c_nationkey)
      inner join nation
              inner join part
              on (part.p_partkey >= part.p_size)
            inner join lineitem
              inner join supplier
                inner join lineitem
                on (lineitem.l_tax > lineitem.l_discount)
              on (lineitem.l_commitdate < lineitem.l_receiptdate)
            on (nation.n_name = lineitem.l_returnflag )
          inner join orders
            inner join orders
              inner join lineitem
              on (lineitem.l_discount = lineitem.l_discount)
            on (orders.o_shippriority < orders.o_custkey)
          on (nation.n_regionkey = orders.o_orderkey )
        inner join partsupp
              inner join part
              on (partsupp.ps_availqty >= partsupp.ps_partkey)
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
          inner join part
          on (part.p_retailprice >= orders.o_totalprice)
        on (lineitem.l_commitdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      on (orders.o_orderdate <= lineitem.l_shipdate)
    on (orders.o_clerk < orders.o_orderstatus)
where region.r_regionkey is NULL;

sql:
select

    cast(cast(null as float8) as float8)), 
  partsupp.ps_suppkey
from 
  region
          inner join supplier
              inner join partsupp
              on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_name)
            inner join region
            on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= partsupp.ps_supplycost)
        inner join part
          inner join orders
          on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = region.r_regionkey)
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
    inner join partsupp
    on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
where partsupp.ps_partkey = partsupp.ps_suppkey

select

from

      inner join orders
        inner join orders
        on (orders.o_totalprice <= orders.o_totalprice)
      on (orders.o_custkey >= orders.o_orderkey)
    inner join part
        inner join lineitem
          inner join partsupp
            inner join orders
              inner join customer
                  inner join region
                  on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
                inner join nation
                on (customer.c_nationkey < nation.n_regionkey)
              on (orders.o_custkey <= nation.n_regionkey)
            on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
          on (lineitem.l_returnflag = customer.c_phone )
        on (orders.o_orderdate = orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join part
      on (nation.n_comment = part.p_name )
    on (orders.o_clerk is NULL)
where part.p_name is not NULL

sql:
select  
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  count(*), 
  nation.n_comment, 
  orders.o_orderstatus, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as int8) as int8)), 
  region.r_comment, 
  customer.c_nationkey, 
  customer.c_mktsegment, 
  customer.c_phone, 
  region.r_regionkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as timetz) as timetz)), 
  orders.o_custkey, 
  partsupp.ps_supplycost, 
  partsupp.ps_availqty, 
  customer.c_custkey
from 
  supplier
      inner join partsupp
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_phone <= supplier.s_phone)
          inner join region
            inner join region
            on (region.r_regionkey > region.r_regionkey)
          on (region.r_name = region.r_name)
        inner join nation
        on (region.r_name > region.r_name)
      on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
    inner join supplier
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_nationkey < supplier.s_suppkey)
          inner join partsupp
          on (supplier.s_suppkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )
        inner join partsupp
        on (partsupp.ps_availqty = partsupp.ps_partkey )
      inner join region
          inner join nation
          on (region.r_comment = nation.n_comment )
        inner join orders
          inner join customer
            inner join nation
            on (nation.n_regionkey > customer.c_nationkey)
          on (customer.c_acctbal < orders.o_totalprice)
        on (orders.o_totalprice = orders.o_totalprice)
      on (customer.c_address = region.r_comment )
    on (nation.n_comment is not NULL)
where supplier.s_comment is NULL
limit 178;
nl: What are the market segments, available quantities, order statuses, and customer information for a specific set of customers, along with their corresponding nation comments, region keys, phone numbers, and supply costs?

      inner join supplier

                on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal )
              on (customer.c_custkey < customer.c_nationkey)
            on (lineitem.l_shipdate >= lineitem.l_commitdate)
          on (lineitem.l_shipmode <= lineitem.l_shipinstruct)
        on (lineitem.l_returnflag > supplier.s_name)
      on (lineitem.l_discount <= lineitem.l_tax)
    inner join region
    on (customer.c_mktsegment <= lineitem.l_linestatus)
where lineitem.l_linenumber is NULL;

sql:
select  
  region.r_name, 
  nation.n_comment
from 
  region
        inner join region
          inner join customer
            inner join supplier
            on (customer.c_acctbal > supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (customer.c_custkey >= supplier.s_suppkey)
        on (customer.c_acctbal < supplier.s_acctbal)
      inner join region
      on (region.r_regionkey = region.r_regionkey )
    inner join customer
        inner join orders
        on (customer.c_acctbal < orders.o_totalprice)
      inner join partsupp
          inner join supplier
              inner join orders
                inner join nation
                on (orders.o_comment = nation.n_comment )
              on (supplier.s_acctbal = supplier.s_acctbal)
            inner join lineitem
              inner join nation
              on (lineitem.l_quantity > lineitem.l_quantity)
            on (orders.o_comment = nation.n_comment )
          on (orders.o_custkey <= lineitem.l_orderkey)
        inner join nation
          inner join lineitem
              inner join region
                inner join customer
                on (customer.c_acctbal >= customer.c_acctbal)
              on (lineitem.l_receiptdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
            inner join orders
            on (lineitem.l_linestatus = orders.o_orderstatus )
          on (orders.o_totalprice >= lineitem.l_discount)
        on (orders.o_shippriority >= region.r_regionkey)
      on (lineitem.l_returnflag > orders.o_orderpriority)
    on (partsupp.ps_comment is NULL)
where customer.c_mktsegment = customer.c_mktsegment;
nl: What regions and national comments are associated with customers in a specific market segment, considering their account balances, order totals, and supplier relationships?

  orders.o_custkey, 
  max(
    cast(cast(null as money) as money)), 
  supplier.s_address,

  partsupp.ps_availqty,

from

          inner join orders
          on (partsupp.ps_comment = orders.o_comment )
        inner join supplier
          inner join lineitem
            inner join region

        on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_commitdate)
      inner join partsupp
      on (lineitem.l_shipdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)

    on (supplier.s_name < supplier.s_phone)

  nation.n_comment
from 
  nation
              inner join region
              on (region.r_regionkey >= region.r_regionkey)
            inner join customer
            on (customer.c_acctbal < customer.c_acctbal)
          inner join part
          on (region.r_regionkey = part.p_partkey )
        inner join nation
        on (part.p_name = nation.n_comment )
      inner join nation
          inner join nation
          on (nation.n_regionkey < nation.n_nationkey)
        inner join region
        on (nation.n_regionkey <= nation.n_nationkey)
      on (part.p_retailprice < customer.c_acctbal)
    inner join partsupp
        inner join partsupp
        on (partsupp.ps_availqty = partsupp.ps_partkey )
      inner join lineitem
          inner join customer
          on (customer.c_nationkey > lineitem.l_linenumber)
        inner join orders
              inner join supplier
              on (orders.o_totalprice < orders.o_totalprice)
            inner join nation
            on (orders.o_orderkey > orders.o_shippriority)
          inner join customer
          on (supplier.s_comment = customer.c_name )
        on (lineitem.l_suppkey < lineitem.l_orderkey)
      on (orders.o_orderdate > orders.o_orderdate)
    on (part.p_comment is not NULL)
where partsupp.ps_availqty < part.p_size

        inner join region
        on (supplier.s_acctbal <= lineitem.l_discount)
      inner join nation
          inner join part
          on (part.p_retailprice <= part.p_retailprice)
        inner join region
              inner join part
              on (region.r_regionkey = part.p_size)
            inner join orders
              inner join customer
              on (customer.c_acctbal = customer.c_acctbal)
            on (orders.o_orderkey >= customer.c_custkey)
          inner join orders

        on (orders.o_orderdate < orders.o_orderdate)
      on (supplier.s_name >= part.p_container)
    inner join part
            inner join customer

          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
        inner join customer
        on (orders.o_orderdate <= orders.o_orderdate)
      inner join lineitem
        inner join customer
            inner join supplier
            on (supplier.s_suppkey > customer.c_custkey)
          inner join partsupp

from

      on (customer.c_acctbal > customer.c_acctbal)
    inner join part
            inner join part

        on (part.p_brand = orders.o_orderstatus )

        inner join partsupp
        on (partsupp.ps_partkey = partsupp.ps_partkey )

select

    cast(cast(null as pg_lsn) as pg_lsn))
from 
  partsupp
        inner join nation
              inner join orders
                inner join region
                on (orders.o_custkey = region.r_regionkey )
              on (region.r_name > nation.n_name)
            inner join nation
            on (region.r_comment = nation.n_comment )
          inner join orders
          on (nation.n_comment = orders.o_comment )
        on (partsupp.ps_suppkey = orders.o_orderkey )
      inner join orders
      on (orders.o_orderstatus < orders.o_orderpriority)
    inner join lineitem
          inner join customer
          on (lineitem.l_shipdate > lineitem.l_shipdate)
        inner join region
            inner join supplier
            on (region.r_name = supplier.s_name )
          inner join orders
          on (orders.o_orderdate >= orders.o_orderdate)
        on (orders.o_orderdate = lineitem.l_shipdate)
      inner join orders
          inner join supplier
            inner join orders
            on (orders.o_totalprice >= supplier.s_acctbal)
          on (orders.o_clerk = orders.o_orderpriority)
        inner join region
        on (orders.o_shippriority = region.r_regionkey )
      on (orders.o_shippriority < orders.o_custkey)
    on (partsupp.ps_supplycost >= lineitem.l_extendedprice)
where region.r_regionkey <= nation.n_nationkey
